{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Dough","content":["Line a baking sheet (approx. 16 in. x 14 in.) with parchment and grease the parchment with olive oil. Set aside.","Place flour, yeast, water, olive oil, sugar and salt into mixing bowl and knead <b>3 min\/<b>.","With aid of oiled spatula transfer dough onto prepared baking sheet. With oiled hands, form dough into a round shape and cover with a thin coating of olive oil. Cover dough with cling wrap or a large bowl and let rise in a warm place until doubled in size (approx. 1 hr.). Meanwhile, preheat oven to 425°F.","Without kneading the dough any further, spread it out with oiled fingertips into a rectangle to fit the baking sheet and set aside."]},{"title":"Topping","content":["Place olive oil, water and salt into mixing bowl and emulsify <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b>.","Add onions and chop <b>6 sec\/speed 4<b> then cook <b>10 min\/212°F\/\/speed 1<b>. Spread on top of dough. Bake for 20-25 minutes (425°F) or until golden brown. Allow to cool before cutting into squares and serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Dough","content":["1 oz olive oil, plus extra to grease","22 oz bread flour","1 oz fresh yeast, crumbled","13 ½ oz water","1 pinch sugar","1 tsp salt"]},{"title":"Topping","content":["3 tbsp extra virgin olive oil","3 tbsp water","1 ½ tsp salt","1 ½ 10 ½ - 12 ½ oz yellow onions, halved"]}],"id":"r91282","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-wxDIunD0HOI\/XZWqpB9bmxI\/AAAAAAAAfbI\/YQDxYM75X68H3AQjoe6jmEkDDGEOUnzywCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_RYwkz_CrUCR1WtKo.png","title":"Focaccia with Onions","publishedAt":"2017-03-24T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"5 g","fat":"6 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"26 g","calories":"766 kJ \/ 183 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking sheet (approx. 16 in. x 14 in.), parchment paper, cling wrap, oven","hintsAndTricks":["<strong>Plain Focaccia with Salt:<\/strong> omit onions and brush oil, water and salt emulsion directly over surface of the dough. Sprinkle with <b>1 tsp coarse<b> salt and bake as directed.","Focaccia can be served with meals or as a sandwich bread.","The dough is quite wet but keeping its surface well oiled prevents it from sticking to fingers.","Use scissors to cut focaccia into squares."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","1h 30m","16 pieces"]}